biosynthesis and accumulation of 1,8-cineole, cypressene, limonene, and 
α-terpineol, Nitrospira and Alphaproteobacteria may play an inhibitory role. 
Finally, our results emphasized the critical role that soil pH and nitrogen 
levels play in driving rhizobacterial community structure, and specific 
functional bacteria can also counteract with soil properties, Acidibacter and 
Nitrospira can affect soil pH and nitrogen effectiveness. Overall, this study 
provides additional insight into the complex correlation of rhizosphere 
microorganisms with bioactive ingredients and soil properties of medicinal 
plants.

